org.overture.core.tests.examples

Class ParamExamplesTest<R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.overture.core.tests.AbsResultTest<R>
      • org.overture.core.tests.examples.ParamExamplesTest<R>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - 

    public abstract class ParamExamplesTest<R>
extends AbsResultTest<R>
    Test on the Overture examples. The behavior of class is very similar to that of ParamStandardTest. The only difference is that the test inputs are not user-configurable. They are provided directly by this class and consist of the standard Overture examples.

    It is recommended that all analysis modules implement a version of this test to ensure that they work on the provided examples.
    Author:
    ldc

      • testData

        public Object[] testData()
                  throws ParserException,
                         LexException,
                         IOException,
                         URISyntaxException
        Provide test data. Provides an array of ExampleSourceData, each holding data (including sources) of an Overture example. Each entry initializes a test for a single Overture example. Test results are derived from the names of the examples and ,by convention, are stored under the src/test/resources/examples folder of each module using this test.
        Returns:
        a collection of ExampleSourceData
        Throws:
        ParserException
        LexException
        IOException
        URISyntaxException

      • testCase

        public void testCase(ExampleSourceData exSource)
              throws FileNotFoundException,
                     IOException,
                     ParserException,
                     LexException
        Execute this test. Takes the model sources, parses, type checks them then takes the AST and applies whatever analysis is implemented in processModel(List). Afterwards, results are compared with AbsResultTest.compareResults(Object, Object).

        If the test is running in update mode, testUpdate(Object) is executed instead of the comparison.
        Parameters:
        exSource - holding the example data. Provided by testData()
        Throws:
        FileNotFoundException
        IOException
        ParserException
        LexException

      • processModel

        public abstract R processModel(List<INode> model)
        Analyse a model. This method is called during test execution to produce the actual result. It must, of course, be overridden to perform whatever analysis the functionality under test performs.

        The output of this method must be of type R, the result type this test runs on. You will will likely need to have a conversion method between the output of your analysis and R.
        Parameters:
        model - the model to process
        Returns:
        the output of the analysis

      • getRelativeExamplesPath

        protected abstract String getRelativeExamplesPath()
        Get the path to the examples. Not all modules that use the test framework are at the same nesting level from core so you must provide the path via this method.

        For reference the examples are in [repository root]/externals/examples/target/code>
        Returns:
        the path to the Overture examples, relative to the current project.
